Description: The return from the Flight into Egypt, with the children killed during the Massacre of the Innocents in the lower right corner, and the young St John the Baptist praying at left; after Francesco Vanni. 1622 Etching
Curator's comments: After F. Vanni's painting in the church of Santi Quirico e Giulitta in Siena.
Subjects: return of the holy family from egypt
Associated names: Representation of: St John the Baptist (Prodromos)
Acquisition name: Bequeathed by: Clayton Mordaunt Cracherode (with Philipe's oval blindstamp with the initials CMC)
